-------|---------|---------|------|\n| Any | 0.8634 | 0.9388 | +0.0754 |\n| Epidural | 0.7731 | 0.9001 | +0.1270 |\n| Intraparenchymal | 0.8956 | 0.9591 | +0.0635 |\n| Intraventricular | 0.9372 | 0.9717 | +0.0345 |\n| Subarachnoid | 0.8322 | 0.8971 | +0.0649 |\n| Subdural | 0.8429 | 0.9213 | +0.0784 |\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Overfitting Prevention Techniques (15 Total)\n\n### Data-Level\n| Technique | Purpose | Status |\n|-----------|---------|--------|\n| WeightedRandomSampler | Balances hemorrhage vs normal draws | ✅ Effective — Epidural AUC reached 0.90 |\n| pos_weight in loss | Penalizes false negatives on rare subtypes | ✅ Effective — all subtypes learning |\n| Label smoothing (ε=0.1) | Prevents overconfidence on noisy labels | ✅ Working silently |\n| PhysioNet domain mixing (5%) | Scanner variation exposure during training | ⏳ Testable on external validation |\n| Data augmentation | Geometric + intensity transforms | ⏳ Measurable with local DHQ dataset |\n\n### Model-Level\n| Technique | Purpose | Status |\n|-----------|---------|--------|\n| Pretrained ImageNet weights | Strong baseline without training from scratch | ✅ Val AUC 0.8574 from Epoch 1 |\n| Progressive dropout (0.3→0.4) | Regularizes classifier head | ✅ Train AUC below Val AUC throughout |\n| BatchNorm1d | Stabilizes feature scale across CT slices | ✅ Stable loss, no spikes |\n| Frozen backbone Phase 1 | Protects pretrained features during head warmup | ✅ Clean Phase 1 convergence |\n\n### Training-Level\n| Technique | Purpose | Status |\n|-----------|---------|--------|\n| Two-phase progressive unfreezing | CT-specific fine-tuning of top MBConv blocks | ✅ +0.0529 Val AUC jump at transition |\n| Low LR in Phase 2 (1e-5) | Prevents large updates on newly unfrozen blocks | ✅ No gradient explosion |\n| Gradient clipping (max_norm=1.0) | Prevents gradient spikes at phase transition | ✅ Clean transition |\n| CosineAnnealingLR | Smooth LR decay | ⏳ Full effect after Epoch 10 |\n| Early stopping (patience=3) | H